{
  "texts": [
    "3)2.2.1 Subcategories P 2 ⊂ [I], SIM ⊂ [I].",
    "Let (P 2 (I), ⊂) be the set of all subsets of I-complexes partially ordered by inclusion.",
    "We view this poset as a category denoted P 2 ⊂ (I) whose objects are I-complexes, i.e.",
    "elements of P 2 (I), denoted X, Y,..., and where there is a unique morphism, represented by the inclusion iX Y ∶ X ↪ Y, if X is included in Y and no morphism if X is not included in Y. P 2⊂ (I) is a subcategory of Pfoot_1 0 whose objects are I-complexes, and where there is a unique morphism of domain X and codomain Y if X ⊂ Y, namely the unique SC-map induced by the identity map on I, and where there is no morphism if X ⊄ Y.We denote by SIM ⊂ [I] the subcategory of P 2 ⊂ [I] with objects the I-simplicial complexes.",
    "P-foundationThe objects of the P-foundation category are p-sites."
  ]
}